post_text:
REMINDER: June 18th from 11 am - 1 pm is our community food distribution. There will be family food boxes along with produce boxes available for pick up from Switzerland County Middle School and Switzerland County Elementary School. This will be a drive up food pick up, volunteers will load your vehicle. The food distribution is open to any Switzerland county resident while supplies last. Please help us pass the word throughout our community by letting your neighbors know.

Upcoming dates for community wide Food Pantry distributions are as follows:

Thursday, June 18th from 11am - 1pm; approximately 240 family food box kits to be distributed

Thursday, June 25th from 11am - 1pm; approximately 240 family food box kits to be distributed

Thursday, July 2nd from 11am - 1pm; approximately 240 family food box kits to be distributed

Distribution locations will be Switzerland County Elementary School and Switzerland County Middle School. As in the past, distribution is first come/first serve.

Thank you for all your support,

Mr. Rod Hite, Superintendent

post_text:
SCHS Celebrating Our Seniors of 2020! Congratulations! Make sure to stop by the school so you can find your graduate!

From Principal David Todd:

The Class of 2020 banners that are in front of the school as well as the large hanging banner were a collective community project. We would like to thank the CFSCI and the VSCF for their generous support of the banners. Thank yous also go out to the local American Legion and the VFW for their support. We also appreciate the help of the Vevay Mercantile. The hanging of the large banner was done by Errol Wayne Judy and Karrie Rayls. Thank you everyone and most importantly, thank you to the Class of 2020 and congratulations. We will see you all on July 18!
text:
SCHS Celebrating Our Seniors of 2020! Congratulations! Make sure to stop by the school so you can find your graduate!

From Principal David Todd:

The Class of 2020 banners that are in front of the school as well as the large hanging banner were a collective community project. We would like to thank the CFSCI and the VSCF for their generous support of the banners. Thank yous also go out to the local American Legion and the VFW for their support. We also appreciate the help of the Vevay Mercantile. The hanging of the large banner was done by Errol Wayne Judy and Karrie Rayls. Thank you everyone and most importantly, thank you to the Class of 2020 and congratulations. We will see you all on July 18!

post_text:
TO: 8th Grade Parents
FROM: Switzerland County Middle School
RE: Washington DC Trip - Cancellation Notice
DATE: April 7th, 2020

Dear Parents,

Due to the concern of the “coronavirus” and the situation that our community, along with the country, finds itself in, the 8th Grade Washington DC Trip scheduled in June has been cancelled.

The school has been in frequent contact with the Ohio Valley Travel Agency (OV Travel). Over the past few weeks we have attempted to negotiate our release from our commitments connected to the trip. At this time, the trip is cancelled. The contract states we will receive a full refund minus $90, which consists of a hotel and the insurance fee. When the refund is returned, we will issue your check.

Any additional individual reservations, outside the group, you may have made you will need to cancel.

We appreciate your patience and understanding. Our decision is in an attempt to come up with the best outcome for everyone involved.

If you have any questions please feel free to contact me.

Thanks,

Sean McGarvey

FROM: Switzerland County Middle School
RE: Washington DC Trip - Cancellation Notice
DATE: April 7th, 2020

Dear Parents,

Due to the concern of the “coronavirus” and the situation that our community, along with the country, finds itself in, the 8th Grade Washington DC Trip scheduled in June has been cancelled.

The school has been in frequent contact with the Ohio Valley Travel Agency (OV Travel). Over the past few weeks we have attempted to negotiate our release from our commitments connected to the trip. At this time, the trip is cancelled. The contract states we will receive a full refund minus $90, which consists of a hotel and the insurance fee. When the refund is returned, we will issue your check.

Any additional individual reservations, outside the group, you may have made you will need to cancel.

We appreciate your patience and understanding. Our decision is in an attempt to come up with the best outcome for everyone involved.

If you have any questions please feel free to contact me.

Thanks,

Sean McGarvey

The sports physical date April 1st at Milan HS is officially cancelled secondary to the Corona Virus (Covid- 19) restrictions that were implemented yesterday at Highpoint Health. We will look to reschedule this event at a later date.



The sports physical date for April 15th at Rising Sun HS is still scheduled, and the status of that event, will be re-evaluated in a couple of weeks.



In so saying, the hospital has implemented several measures which is inclusive of but not limited to: closing down several off site facilities, putting in strict access restrictions, placed a halt on any elective surgeries etc. many if not most of these measures are being implemented today through tomorrow. The restrictions will be in place thru April 3rd.



Thank you for your consideration,



Ed



Edward L. Brush M.S.PT ATC/L | Director of Rehab Services

Office| 812.537.8146

Fax| 812.539.3607



Highpoint Health

600 Wilson Creek Road|Lawrenceburg, IN 47025

Switzerland County is promoting healthy best practices.

* Wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds.

* If soap and water are not available, use an alcohol-based hand sanitizer.

* Avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth with unwashed hands.

* Avoid close contact with people who are sick.

* Stay home when you are sick.

* Cover your cough or sneeze with a tissue, then throw the tissue in the trash.

* Clean and disinfect frequently touched objects and surfaces.

From Coach Eric Cole:
Congratulations these 9 outstanding Pacers are on the all conference team. Allison Furnish and Adrian Armstrong were the meet Most Valuable Swimmers each winning 4 events.

Individual race winners:
Alisha Detmer in the 200 freestyle
Ally Furnish in the 50 Free and 100 Free
Adrian Armstrong in the 200 IM in school record time and in the 500 free
Nathan Furnish in the 50 free
Julio Regueira in the 100 free

Relay wins
Girls 200 free relay and 400 free relay swam by Alisha Detmer Brooke Johnson Deanna Voris and Ally Furnish.
Boys 200 free relay in a new school record time swam by Nathan Furnish Micheal Stanton Julio Regueria and Adrian Armstrong in the race as the lead off swimmer Adrian also broke the 50 free school record.
The boys 400 free relay smashed the old school record by nearly 3 seconds in the win. Nathan Julio and Adrian were joined by JW Goldsberry.

As a coach I could not be prouder of these outstanding student athletes. Now it is on to sectional.

From HS Advisor Kodi Thayer:

On Saturday, December 7, the members from the High School BPA chapter participated in the Regional Leadership Conference which was held at the Ivy Tech in Madison, Indiana. We had 14 students participate and eight of those students will advance to state. Those advancing to state include:
Carly Bennett – 1st in Personal Financial Management & 4th in Banking and Finance, Brooke Johnson – 1st in Advanced Spreadsheet & 3rd in Fundamental Accounting, Austin Bosaw, Ben Hicks, Ben Smith – 2nd in Economic Research Team, Braydan Allen – 3rd in Presentation Management Individual, Annabelle Bear – 3rd in Medical Office Procedures, Ben Smith – 3rd in Business Law and Ethics, Ethan Hussong – 4th in Fundamental Desktop Publishing
To read the full article and see other placements, please click the link https://docs.google.com/document/d/162mEmmTfYpBCSst23xHJFQxnZviC67Q_mox4Dchz5b4/edit?usp=sharing

Switzerland County School Corporation will be on a 2 hour delay Wednesday Sept. 18th for teacher professional development.
Please plan accordingly, your bus will arrive 2 hours later than normal. Students will release at normal time in the afternoon.

The change to the 2 hour delay this year instead of our past 2 hour early release schedule was in an effort to help afternoon career center students and prevent make up days in the event of inclement weather during the winter months professional development sessions.

Please remember we have 2 hour delay professional development sessions built in the calendar on Sept. 18th, Nov. 13th, Feb. 12th, and April 15th.

Pacer Fans:
Please be aware of some very important information pertaining to our varsity football team and schedule that is coming up.

1. Our football conference, MIFC, consists of Milan, North Decatur, South Decatur, Oldenburg, Edinburgh, and Switzerland County. It was decided within the conference to charge a $6.00 admission for all varsity football games. Therefore, the home games (Milan and Edinburgh) and away games (North Decatur, South Decatur, Oldenburg) will be a $6.00 entry fee. Next year, all home games will be $6.00.

2. Our Oldenburg away game on September 20th will be played at Elder High School in Cincinnati, Ohio. The address to Elder High School is the following...3900 Vincent Ave, Cincinnati, OH 45205

3. If you have a season pass for our SCHS home events, Oldenburg Academy will honor and allow you to use them on September 20th at Elder High School; therefore, be sure to bring your All-Sports passes for this game if you have one.

Thanks and Go Pacers!!!

post_text:
FAFSA on Wheels- Tuesday, July 30th 3:00-6:00 pm
Interested in taking college classes in the fall at Ivy Tech Madison? Come join us at the Switzerland County Technology and Education Center (TEC) to get assistance with filing your FAFSA out and have your enrollment questions answered!

Items to bring:

Social Security Number
Driver’s License
Income tax returns, W-2 forms, and 1099 forms from 2017 (if you are married, you will also need your spouse’s)
Records and documentation of other untaxed income (social security, welfare, etc.)
Current bank account and brokerage statements
Business or farm records
Questions? Contact Courtney Gullion at 8120265-2580 ext 4128 or cgullion1@ivytech.edu

post_text:
Please come and join us at Switzerland County Middle School on Tuedsay, August 6th from 6:00-8:00pm as we host Middle School Open House.

Students who will be in 7th and 8th Grade for the upcoming school year along with their parents and family members are welcome to attend along with any other community members who are interested in our school.

Students and parents will have the opportunity to meet school personnel (including Administration, School Counselor, Teachers, and Office Staff) and tour the building to learn where lockers and classrooms are located.

The doors will open at 6:00pm and there will be PowerPoint Presentation detailing important school information starting at 6:15pm in the gym that all parents and students are welcome to attend. After this you will have the opportunity to register on Skyward with the assistance of school personnel along with being able to pay all technology and textbook fees that night as well.

We hope you can join us on Tuesday, August 6th starting at 6:00pm for this very important night!

Sincerely,
MS Administration and Staff

post_text:
ILEARN Testing starts up at Switzerland County Middle School this coming Monday, May 6th and will continue throughout the rest of the week (May 6th-10th). As we get ready to start the test next week please avoid any absences on testing days and please avoid outside appointments for the testing times which will be in the morning. Also, remember that all Chromebooks will be staying at school each night next week so they can be fully charged and ready to go for each day of testing. The Chromebooks will actually be kept at the MS starting tomorrow night Friday, May 3rd so they will be ready to go Monday morning.

We've tried to prepare students well; ILEARN results are important to our school's success, although we all know that our students have far more talents than what is reflected in those numbers. All we ask is for the students to be here and try their best!!!
